| `.some()`  | OR           | At least one condition is `true` | First `true` |
| `.every()` | AND (`&amp;&amp;`)         | All conditions are `true` | First `false` |                                  |              |
</md></sn><sn><md>### Conclusion

Both `.some()` and `.every()` are powerful tools for performing logical checks on arrays.

* Use **`.some()`** when you need to know if **any** element meets a condition.
* Use **`.every()`** when you must ensure **all** elements meet a condition.

These methods make your code cleaner, more readable, and efficient when working with logical evaluations or filtering arrays.
